In re BROWN. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. October 30, 1902.) Nos. 71, 76. Appeals from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York.

Before WALLACE, TOWNSEND, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The motion to dismiss appeals from orders of the district court of April 26, 1902, and May 17, 1902, are respectively granted, with costs.
